Use a hashmap to store each number's complement (target - num) as you iterate. For each number, check if it already exists in the map. If yes, return the pair.

function twoSum(nums: number[], target: number): [number, number] {
  const seen = new Map<number, number>();
  for (const num of nums) {
    const complement = target - num;
    if (seen.has(complement)) {
      return [complement, num];
    }
    seen.set(num, complement);
  }
  throw new Error('No solution found');
}

Time complexity: O(n) — single pass through the array.
Space complexity: O(n) — hashmap stores at most n entries.

