modelAnswer:
Approach 1 (HashMap): Count character frequencies in both strings and compare the maps.

function areAnagrams(s1: string, s2: string): boolean {
  const normalize = (s: string) => s.toLowerCase().replace(/\s/g, '');
  const a = normalize(s1);
  const b = normalize(s2);
  if (a.length !== b.length) return false;
  const freq = new Map<string, number>();
  for (const ch of a) freq.set(ch, (freq.get(ch) || 0) + 1);
  for (const ch of b) {
    const count = freq.get(ch);
    if (!count) return false;
    freq.set(ch, count - 1);
  }
  return true;
}

Approach 2 (Sort): Sort both strings and compare. Simpler code but O(n log n).

Time complexity: O(n) for hashmap approach, O(n log n) for sorting.
Space complexity: O(n) for the frequency map or sorted copies.

