modelAnswer:
Sort each string to create a canonical key, then group by that key:

function groupAnagrams(strs: string[]): string[][] {
  const map = new Map<string, string[]>();
  for (const s of strs) {
    const key = s.split('').sort().join('');
    if (!map.has(key)) map.set(key, []);
    map.get(key)!.push(s);
  }
  return Array.from(map.values());
}

Time complexity: O(n * k log k) where n is the number of strings and k is the maximum string length (due to sorting each string).
Space complexity: O(n * k) to store all strings in the hashmap.

Alternative: Use character frequency as key (e.g., '1#0#0#...#2') to avoid sorting — O(n * k) time.

